main event: A civilian woman in Albany, New York spotted a circular-shaped object that circled once and then headed north on October 6, 1952.
interesting points: The object was observed for 30 seconds and moved at an unusually fast speed.
The sighting occurred 44 minutes after the USDA in Albany released a pinair.
There were no other known objects in the area at the time of the sighting.
The report includes a coded message with additional details about the sighting.
